Description: If Product Type is Swap and in Interest rate class, check for pay leg type and rec leg type. If one of them is fixed, then it is IR_Swap_Fixed_Float
Do as above. If both legs are float, then it is IR_Swap_Basis
If Product Type is Swap and is in Interest Rate Class, if the notional is Bullet then it is a standard swap (one of the above), else it is a Amortising/accreting swap, IR_Swap_Amortising
If Product Type is FRA in Calypso and is in MM class, then it is IR_FRA
